solution: class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> constructRectangle(int area) {
        int w = static_cast<int>(sqrt(area));
        while (area % w != 0) --w;
        return {area / w, w};
    }
};
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(sqrt(area))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Start with the integer closest to sqrt(area) as width, then decrement until it divides area; the corresponding length is area/width. This minimizes L-W difference while satisfying L>=W.

